Some 2,000 residents flocked to the Migori Stadium in a last-minute push to apply for ID cards. The scene looked like a gospel crusade.Across the eight subcounties, registrars have been overwhelmed by the huge number of residents, estimated to be more than 30,000, seeking IDs.On Wednesday the Huduma Centre was filled with residents seeking IDs and registering as voters, forcing officials to send some home. This has led to fears of voter apathy and potential voters being locked out of registration.&ldquo;We are overwhelmed by the huge numbers of those seeking to get national identification cards, my officers are stretched to the limit,&rdquo; Seth Mboya, the county registrar, said. On Wednesday the system at Oyani Maasai centre, Uriri constituency, broke down and residents were turned away.